properties.areaDesc: Willapa Hills; Coast Range of Northwest Oregon
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 12:13AM PST until January 13 at 6:00AM PST by NWS Portland OR
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 1 to 4 inches.
Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...In Washington, the Willapa Hills. In Oregon, the Coast
Range of Northwest Oregon.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on snow covered roads, including Highways 6 and
26 across the Northwest Oregon Coast Range, and Washington
Highway 4 over KM Mountain. Roads will likely remain slippery
into the Monday morning commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Heaviest snow accumulations will be above
1000 feet.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM PST MONDAY
